attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, SPARC, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a MIPS-based ELF, likely a component of a DDoS botnet. It contains strings to perform SSDP (Simple Service Discovery Protocol) network discovery, a technique commonly used for propagation or conducting SSDP amplification DDoS attacks. Key IOCs include the SSDP M-SEARCH request string "M-SEARCH * HTTP/1.1\r\nHOST: 255.255.255.255:1900..." and a hardcoded User-Agent "Google Chrome/60.0.3112.90 Windows" to masquerade its network activity. The extensive use of complex, unstructured functions suggests code obfuscation to hinder analysis.
